summary: An FBI electronic communication documenting the transfer of original ELSUR (Electronic Surveillance) evidence from the Washington Field Office to the Miami Field Office for permanent storage. The evidence pertains to two FBI cases involving Jeffrey Epstein and Alfredo Rodriguez.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: Named as the subject of FBI case 31E-MM-108062, for which ELSUR evidence is being transferred.

persons.name: Alfredo Rodriguez
persons.context: Named as the subject of FBI case 72-MM-113327, for which ELSUR evidence is being transferred. The document references a related sub-file.

connections.description: Both are subjects of separate but related FBI investigations, as evidenced by the coordinated transfer of their ELSUR evidence under the same communication.

events.title: Transfer of ELSUR Evidence to Miami
events.description: The Washington Field Office ELSUR Unit ships original electronic surveillance evidence to the Miami Field Office ELSUR Unit via FedEx for permanent storage.

keyFacts: The document is an FBI record dated May 15, 2025, concerning the handling of sensitive investigative material (ELSUR).
It confirms the existence of at least two active FBI case files related to Jeffrey Epstein (31E-MM-108062) and Alfredo Rodriguez (72-MM-113327) as of that date.
Original physical evidence from electronic surveillance is being transferred from Washington, D.C. to Miami for permanent storage, indicating Miami's role as the custodian for these investigations.
The evidence for Epstein's case is listed as one item (1D1), while Rodriguez's case involves six items (1D1-1D6).
The document is labeled as pertaining to a 'SENSITIVE INVESTIGATIVE MATTER,' highlighting the classified nature of the operations.
